The paper deals with the Price of Anarchy (PoA) in markets, which is a concept studied in game theory and algorithmic game theory. Therefore, cs.GT (Game Theory and Mechanism Design) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses large markets and their behavior, which could fall under cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper's focus on auctions and markets suggests cs.EC (Economics and Computation) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper's use of utility functions and optimization could also place it in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
